application/json.name: application/json

utc.name: utc
utc.description: Time given as UTC instead of local (default is false)?

codeType.name: codeType
codeType.description: Type of any given codes: 'IATA', 'ICAO', or 'FS'. If not specified all domains will be searched in the order stated.

extendedOptions.name: extendedOptions
extendedOptions.description: Extended options for modifying standard API behavior to fit special use cases. Options: 'useInlinedReferences', 'useHttpErrors', 'includeDeltas'.

methods.description: Returns the Flight Statuses for the given Carrier and Flight Number that departed on the given date. Optionally, the arrival airport may be specified.

application/json.name: application/json

utc.name: utc
utc.description: Time given as UTC instead of local (default is false)?

codeType.name: codeType
codeType.description: Type of any given codes: 'IATA', 'ICAO', or 'FS'. If not specified all domains will be searched in the order stated.

extendedOptions.name: extendedOptions
extendedOptions.description: Extended options for modifying standard API behavior to fit special use cases. Options: 'useInlinedReferences', 'useHttpErrors', 'includeDeltas'.

methods.description: Returns the Flight Statuses for the given Carrier and Flight Number that departed on the given date. Optionally, the departure airport may be specified.

utc.name: utc
utc.description: Time given as UTC instead of local (default is false)

numHours.name: numHours
numHours.description: Number of hours' worth of departures to include (up to 24).

maxPositions.name: maxPositions
maxPositions.description: Maximum number of positions in track

maxPositionAgeMinutes.name: maxPositionAgeMinutes
maxPositionAgeMinutes.description: Maximum age for positions in track (minutes)

codeType.name: codeType
codeType.example: Type of any given codes: 'IATA', 'ICAO', or 'FS'. If not specified, all domains will be searched in the order stated.

extendedOptions.name: extendedOptions
extendedOptions.example: Extended options for modifying standard API behavior to fit special use cases. Options: 'useInlinedReferences', 'useHttpErrors', 'includeDeltas'.

methods.description: Returns the positional tracks of flights, with a given carrier and flight number, arriving or having arrived on the given date. If 'hourOfDay' is specified, results will be limited to the given hour, unless 'numHours' is also specified. Arrival airport may optionally be specified. Flight plans may be optionally included. To narrow down to only the freshest data, you may optionally limit the age (in minutes) and/or number of positions per track.

utc.name: utc

numHours.name: numHours
numHours.description: Number of hours' worth of departures to include (up to 24).

maxPositions.name: maxPositions
maxPositions.description: Maximum number of positions in track

maxPositionAgeMinutes.name: maxPositionAgeMinutes
maxPositionAgeMinutes.description: Maximum age for positions in track (minutes)

codeType.name: codeType
codeType.example: Type of any given codes: 'IATA', 'ICAO', or 'FS'. If not specified, all domains will be searched in the order stated.

extendedOptions.name: extendedOptions
extendedOptions.example: Extended options for modifying standard API behavior to fit special use cases. Options: 'useInlinedReferences', 'useHttpErrors', 'includeDeltas'.

methods.description: Returns the positional tracks of flights, with a given carrier and flight number, departing or having departed on the given date. If 'hourOfDay' is specified, results will be limited to the given hour, unless 'numHours' is also specified. Departure airport may optionally be specified. Flight plans may be optionally included. To narrow down to only the freshest data, you may optionally limit the age (in minutes) or number of positions per track.

application/json.name: application/json

utc.name: utc
utc.description: Time given as UTC instead of local (default is false)

numHours.name: numHours
numHours.description: Number of hours' worth of departures to include (up to 6; default is 1)

carrier.name: carrier
carrier.description: Filter results to include only the carrier indicated

codeType.name: codeType
codeType.description: Type of any given codes: 'IATA', 'ICAO', or 'FS'. If not specified, all domains will be searched in the order stated.

maxFlights.name: maxFlights
maxFlights.description: The maximum number of unique flights to return status documents for. This is used to restrict output size for the API documentation; if it is omitted, all flights are returned.

extendedOptions.name: extendedOptions
extendedOptions.description: Extended options for modifying standard API behavior to fit special use cases. Options: 'useInlinedReferences', 'useHttpErrors', 'includeDeltas'.

methods.description: Returns the status of all flights departing (or having departed) from an airport within the specified hour, or within a window up to 6 hours wide if numHours is specified.

application/json.name: application/json

utc.name: utc
utc.description: Time given as UTC instead of local (default is false)

numHours.name: numHours
numHours.description: Number of hours' worth of departures to include (up to 6; default is 1)

carrier.name: carrier
carrier.description: Filter results to include only the carrier indicated

codeType.name: codeType
codeType.description: Type of any given codes: 'IATA', 'ICAO', or 'FS'. If not specified, all domains will be searched in the order stated.

maxFlights.name: maxFlights
maxFlights.description: The maximum number of unique flights to return status documents for. This is used to restrict output size for the API documentation; if it is omitted, all flights are returned.

extendedOptions.name: extendedOptions
extendedOptions.description: Extended options for modifying standard API behavior to fit special use cases. Options: 'useInlinedReferences', 'useHttpErrors', 'includeDeltas'.

methods.description: Returns the status of all flights arriving (or having arrived) at an airport within the specified hour, or within a window up to 6 hours wide if numHours is specified.

application/json.name: application/json

carrier.name: carrier
carrier.description: Filter results to include only the carrier indicated

codeType.name: codeType
codeType.description: Type of any given codes: 'IATA', 'ICAO', or 'FS'. If not specified, all domains will be searched in the order stated.

maxFlights.name: maxFlights
maxFlights.description: The maximum number of unique flights to return status documents for. This is used to restrict output size for the API documentation; if it is omitted, all flights are returned.

extendedOptions.name: extendedOptions
extendedOptions.description: Extended options for modifying standard API behavior to fit special use cases. Options: 'useInlinedReferences', 'useHttpErrors', 'includeDeltas'.

maxPositions.name: maxPositions
maxPositions.description: Maximum number of positions in each track (per source)

maxPositionAgeMinutes.name: maxPositionAgeMinutes
maxPositionAgeMinutes.description: Maximum age (in minutes) for positions to include

methods.description: Returns the positional tracks of active flights having the specified arrival airport. Flight plans may be optionally included. "Active" flights are those for which positional data are available, and which have not yet landed. To narrow down to only the freshest data, you may optionally limit the age (in minutes) and/or number of positions per track.

carrier.name: carrier
carrier.description: Filter results to include only the carrier indicated

codeType.name: codeType
codeType.description: Type of any given codes: 'IATA', 'ICAO', or 'FS'. If not specified, all domains will be searched in the order stated.

maxFlights.name: maxFlights
maxFlights.description: The maximum number of unique flights to return status documents for. This is used to restrict output size for the API documentation; if it is omitted, all flights are returned.

extendedOptions.name: extendedOptions
extendedOptions.description: Extended options for modifying standard API behavior to fit special use cases. Options: 'useInlinedReferences', 'useHttpErrors', 'includeDeltas'.

maxPositions.name: maxPositions
maxPositions.description: Maximum number of positions in each track (per source)

maxPositionAgeMinutes.name: maxPositionAgeMinutes
maxPositionAgeMinutes.description: Maximum age (in minutes) for positions to include

methods.description: Returns the positional tracks of active flights having the specified departure airport. Flight plans may be optionally included. "Active" flights are those for which positional data are available, and which have not yet landed. To narrow down to only the freshest data, you may optionally limit the age (in minutes) and/or number of positions per track.'

utc.name: utc
utc.description: Time given as UTC instead of local (default is false)

numHours.name: numHours
numHours.description: Number of hours' worth of departures to include (up to 24).

codeType.name: codeType
codeType.example: Type of any given codes: 'IATA', 'ICAO', or 'FS'. If not specified, all domains will be searched in the order stated.

extendedOptions.name: extendedOptions
extendedOptions.example: Extended options for modifying standard API behavior to fit special use cases. Options: 'useInlinedReferences', 'useHttpErrors', 'includeDeltas'.

maxFlights.name: maxFlights
maxFlights.description: The maximum number of unique flights to return tracks for. This is used to restrict output size for the API documentation.

methods.description: Returns the status of all flights for a given route arriving on the specified date

application/xml.name: application/xml
application/xml.schemaContent:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<xsd:schema xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <xsd:element name="response">
    <xsd:complexType>
      <xsd:sequence>
        <xsd:element name="appendix" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:string"/>
        <xsd:element name="flightPositions" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1">
          <xsd:complexType>
            <xsd:sequence>
              <xsd:element name="flightPosition" maxOccurs="unbounded">
                <xsd:complexType>
                  <xsd:sequence>
                    <xsd:element name="flightId" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:int"/>
                    <xsd:element name="callsign" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:normalizedString"/>
                    <xsd:element name="heading" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:decimal"/>
                    <xsd:element name="source" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:normalizedString"/>
                    <xsd:element name="positions" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1">
                      <xsd:complexType>
                        <xsd:sequence>
                          <xsd:element name="position" maxOccurs="unbounded">
                            <xsd:complexType>
                              <xsd:sequence>
                                <xsd:element name="lon" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:decimal"/>
                                <xsd:element name="lat" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:decimal"/>
                                <xsd:element name="speedMph" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:int"/>
                                <xsd:element name="altitudeFt" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:int"/>
                                <xsd:element name="source" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:normalizedString"/>
                                <xsd:element name="date" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:normalizedString"/>
                              </xsd:sequence>
                            </xsd:complexType>
                          </xsd:element>
                        </xsd:sequence>
                      </xsd:complexType>
                    </xsd:element>
                  </xsd:sequence>
                </xsd:complexType>
              </xsd:element>
            </xsd:sequence>
          </xsd:complexType>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="request" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1">
          <xsd:complexType>
            <xsd:sequence>
              <xsd:element name="url" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:anyURI"/>
              <xsd:element name="topLatitude" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1">
                <xsd:complexType>
                  <xsd:sequence>
                    <xsd:element name="requested" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:decimal"/>
                    <xsd:element name="interpreted" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:decimal"/>
                  </xsd:sequence>
                </xsd:complexType>
              </xsd:element>
              <xsd:element name="leftLongitude" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1">
                <xsd:complexType>
                  <xsd:sequence>
                    <xsd:element name="requested" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:decimal"/>
                    <xsd:element name="interpreted" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:decimal"/>
                  </xsd:sequence>
                </xsd:complexType>
              </xsd:element>
              <xsd:element name="bottomLatitude" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1">
                <xsd:complexType>
                  <xsd:sequence>
                    <xsd:element name="requested" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:decimal"/>
                    <xsd:element name="interpreted" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:decimal"/>
                  </xsd:sequence>
                </xsd:complexType>
              </xsd:element>
              <xsd:element name="rightLongitude" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1">
                <xsd:complexType>
                  <xsd:sequence>
                    <xsd:element name="requested" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:decimal"/>
                    <xsd:element name="interpreted" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:decimal"/>
                  </xsd:sequence>
                </xsd:complexType>
              </xsd:element>
              <xsd:element name="maxFlights" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:string"/>
              <xsd:element name="extendedOptions" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:string"/>
            </xsd:sequence>
          </xsd:complexType>
        </xsd:element>
      </xsd:sequence>
    </xsd:complexType>
  </xsd:element>
</xsd:schema>

methods.description: Get flights centered around a particular point, within a given radius. The area searched is a square (not circle); the radius specifies the distance from the center of the square to one of its corners. Center point is specified in degrees of latitude and longitude; radius is specified in miles.

<xsd:schema xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">

        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="departureDate" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1">

        </xsd:element>

        <xsd:element name="heading" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:decimal"/>
        <xsd:element name="positions" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1">
          <xsd:complexType>
            <xsd:sequence>
              <xsd:element name="position" maxOccurs="unbounded">
                <xsd:complexType>
                  <xsd:sequence>
                    <xsd:element name="lon" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:decimal"/>
                    <xsd:element name="lat" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:decimal"/>
                    <xsd:element name="speedMph" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:int"/>
                    <xsd:element name="altitudeFt" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:int"/>
                    <xsd:element name="source" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:normalizedString"/>
                    <xsd:element name="date" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:normalizedString"/>
                  </xsd:sequence>
                </xsd:complexType>
              </xsd:element>
            </xsd:sequence>
          </xsd:complexType>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="waypoints" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1">
          <xsd:complexType>
            <xsd:sequence>
              <xsd:element name="waypoint" maxOccurs="unbounded">
                <xsd:complexType>
                  <xsd:sequence>
                    <xsd:element name="lon" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:decimal"/>
                    <xsd:element name="lat" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:decimal"/>
                  </xsd:sequence>
                </xsd:complexType>
              </xsd:element>
            </xsd:sequence>
          </xsd:complexType>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="legacyRoute" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" type="xsd:normalizedString"/>
      </xsd:sequence>
    </xsd:complexType>
  </xsd:element>
</xsd:schema>

airport.name: airport
airport.description: Optional airport filter to restrict results to a single airport

codeType.name: codeType
codeType.description: Type of any given codes: 'IATA', 'ICAO', or 'FS'. If not specified all domains will be searched in the order stated.

maxFlights.name: maxFlights
maxFlights.description: The maximum number of unique flights to return status documents for. This is used to restrict output size for the API documentation.

extendedOptions.name: extendedOptions
extendedOptions.description: Extended options for modifying standard API behavior to fit special use cases. Options: 'useInlinedReferences', 'useHttpErrors', 'includeDeltas'.

maxPositions.name: maxPositions
maxPositions.description: Maximum number of positions in track

maxPositionAgeMinutes.name: maxPositionAgeMinutes
maxPositionAgeMinutes.description: Maximum age (in minutes) for positions to include

methods.description: Returns the positional tracks of active flights for a fleet. Flight plans may be optionally included. "Active" flights are those for which positional data are available, and which have not yet landed. To narrow down to only the freshest data, you may optionally limit the age (in minutes) or number of positions per track.

application/json.name: application/json

utc.name: utc
utc.description: Time given as UTC instead of local (default is false)

numHours.name: numHours
numHours.description: Number of hours worth of departures to include (up to 24)

airport.name: airport
airport.description: Optional airport filter to restrict results to a single airport

codeType.name: codeType
codeType.description: Type of any given codes: 'IATA', 'ICAO', or 'FS'. If not specified all domains will be searched in the order stated.

maxFlights.name: maxFlights
maxFlights.description: The maximum number of unique flights to return status documents for. This is used to restrict output size for the API documentation.

extendedOptions.name: extendedOptions
extendedOptions.description: Extended options for modifying standard API behavior to fit special use cases. Options: 'useInlinedReferences', 'useHttpErrors', 'includeDeltas'.

methods.description: Returns the status of all flights for a fleet departing or having departed on the given date (UTC). If 'hourOfDay' is specified, results will be limited to the given hour, unless 'numHours' is also specified.
